    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="691"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ascertain damages for outbreaks at both Harpoot and Marash as soon as possible,
                    but on such satisfactory evidence that demand can not be objected to as
                    excessive. Cable amounts as soon as ascertained. Have you convincing evidence of
                    complicity or connivance in outrages by responsible Turkish officials? Are
                    American citizens at Marash in special danger or accessible by mail, telegraph,
                    or otherwise from Alexandretta, and do they or any part of them desire to reach
                    coast; and if so, has adequate escort been asked and refused? Your 698
                    received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
